1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
CD4+ T cells drive immune regulation — but a screen alone can't tell you what's druggable.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:20,000
We joined the GWT screen with external public databases into one verifiable method.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Two independent funnels — readiness and drug-deliverability — intersect on five core targets.

4
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Adjust a weight, reset it, search PLCG1 — the ranking reacts live; the evidence never does.

5
00:00:47,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Every target has its own dossier — effect size, downstream breadth, cross-donor robustness, all inspectable.

6
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Side by side, the five core targets show distinct evidence strength and risk trade-offs.

7
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Switch to the clinician's view: concept, disease, drug, population genetics, expression — strong effect is neither safety nor clinical efficacy.

8
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Change a condition or threshold — the figure updates live, proving context-sensitivity.

9
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Open Targets re-verifies all 55, STRING recovers known partners, an HIV screen lines up too.

10
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:15,000
The targets most valuable to researchers are often the ones clinicians must watch most closely.

11
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:25,000
From 22M cells to 7,249 targets — the full curation and analysis pipeline, laid out.

12
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:43,000
The gallery is publication-ready, the docs explain operation, and the API lets other teams reuse our evidence directly.

13
00:02:43,000 --> 00:03:00,000
We close on provenance — versions, coverage, and the source behind every conclusion, all traceable.
